EntityMetaData.name: global-sample.xaction
EntityMetaData.description: This is an example of using a global filter and a session filter. <p/>The global filter is DEPARTMENT_LIST which provides values for the DEPARTMENT parameter. DEPARTMENT_LIST is generated by doing an SQL 'select distinct' on the departments column. Being a global filter, the query is executed only once and available to all users. <p/>The session filter REGION_FILTER is generated by a rule that is executed for each user that logs in. The values are stored in the user's session and is available as long as the user remains logged in.
EntityMetaData.title: Secure Session and Global Filters

EntityMetaData.name: quadrant-budget-for-region-session.xaction
EntityMetaData.description:
This is an example of a secure parameterized PDF report.

Valid entries are defined by a business rule executed during login and saved in the user's session.

If you are logged in as 'Suzy', you will be prompted to select a region filtered for her - 'Eastern', 'Western' and 'Southern'. Log in as 'admin' who only has permission for 'Central' and you will not be prompted
EntityMetaData.title: Secured PDF Example

EntityMetaData.name: secure-sample.xaction
EntityMetaData.description: This is an example of a report that requires 2 parameters; Region and Department.<p/>The Region selections are defined by a business rule executed during login and saved in the user's session.<p/>The Department values are hard coded in the Action Sequence document.
EntityMetaData.title: Two filter sets, secure and hard coded
